  "scriptText": "PART 1\n\nINT. LIVING ROOM - DAY\n\nThe camera lingers on a messy coffee table. A hand with bitten fingernails reaches into a crinkly chip bag. SFX: LOUD, RUSTLING PLASTIC.\nThe camera DOLLIES BACK AND TILTS UP, following the hand to MARK’S face. He’s mid-chew, looking utterly vacant. He stares at the TV off-screen. SFX: A CRUNCH SO LOUD IT FEELS INTIMATE.\n\nMARK\n(Mumbling through chips)\nFinally. No notifications. Just peace.\n\nHe uses his t-shirt to wipe salt off his thumb. The camera PANS SLOWLY to his left, catching the dust motes dancing in the sun. Mark exhales, a long, heavy sound of a man who has finally clocked out of reality.\n\nMARK\nNo filters. No bullshit. Perfect.\n\nHe reaches for the coffee mug, his movement slow and heavy. The camera CIRCLES BEHIND his head, showing the messy crown of his hair against the backdrop of the cluttered room. As he brings the mug to his lips, he pauses, hearing a faint, digital chirp from the hallway.\n\nPART 2\n\nINT. LIVING ROOM - CONTINUOUS\n\nThe camera continues its slow, rhythmic orbit around the sofa. MARK is just settling into his sigh of relief. He reaches for the coffee mug, his movement slow and heavy. As he brings the mug to his lips, he pauses, hearing a faint, digital chirp from the hallway.\n\nSuddenly, DAVE strides into the frame from the hallway. He looks sharp, vibrant, and offensively clean. He winces as he looks at Mark’s wrinkled shirt.\n\nDAVE\nSip looks messy. Try this.\n\nMARK\n(Jerking upright, startled)\nWait, what—? Dave?\n\nDAVE\n(Pushing Mark’s shoulder to the side)\nI’m you, minus the pores.\n\nDave sits down on the cushion. SFX: A CLEAN, DIGITAL \"POP\" SOUND. Unlike Mark, Dave doesn't sink into the sofa; he stays \"on top\" of it.\n\nMARK\n(Squeezed against the armrest)\nI like my pores. Get out.\n\nDAVE\n(Straightening his own perfect hair)\nThe audience doesn’t. Move over.\n\nMARK\nThis is my couch, man!\n\nDAVE\n(Adjusting Mark’s crooked glasses with a finger)\nIt’s \"unverified\" content, Mark. Be grateful.\n\nThe camera PULLS BACK slightly as they bicker, framing both versions in a MEDIUM SHOT. MARK looks exhausted, while DAVE is practically glowing. \n\nMARK opens his mouth to argue further, but a wet, heavy THUD from the coffee table interrupts him.\n\nPART 3\n\nINT. LIVING ROOM - CONTINUOUS\n\nMARK opens his mouth to argue further, but a wet, heavy THUD from the coffee table interrupts him. \nThe camera captures the coffee table shaking from a sudden impact. LUCAS (Animated Frog) is suddenly there, standing on a pile of Mark's mail. SFX: A WET, SQUELCHING THUD.\n\nDAVE\n(Recoiling)\nHey! I’m in the middle—\n\nLUCAS\nHuman likeness flagged. Too sensitive.\n\nLUCAS hops from the table to the sofa. SFX: THE COUCH SPRINGS GROAN. The impact sends MARK sliding off the cushion and onto the hardwood floor. VFX: THE CAMERA SHAKES ON LANDING.\n\nMARK\n(From the floor)\nA frog? Seriously?\n\nLUCAS\n(Looking down at Mark)\nLow risk. High engagement.\n\nDAVE\n(Gesturing to his face)\nBut I’m optimized! Look!\n\nLUCAS\n(Turning to Dave)\nHair is a liability. Move.\n\nLUCAS physically shoves DAVE with a webbed hand. DAVE slides to the very edge of the frame. The camera ZOOMS IN slightly on Lucas, who now owns the center of the sofa, looking majestic and immovable.\n\nPART 4\n\nINT. LIVING ROOM - CONTINUOUS\n\nLUCAS (CONT'D)\n(Turning to Dave)\nMove.\n\nLUCAS sits majestically. He spots a loose potato chip on the table. SFX: A WHIP-LIKE SNAP. His tongue shoots out and pulls the chip into his mouth.\n\nMARK\n(From the floor)\nThose were my organic chips.\n\nLUCAS\n(Chewing slowly)\nOptimizing the content, Mark.\n\nDAVE\n(Whispering to Mark)\nHe has better engagement metrics.\n\nMark looks at Dave, then back at the frog. He looks at his own hands, then at the mess on the floor.\n\nMARK\nI'm going for a walk.\n\nMark starts to stand up. SFX: A LOUD, STATIC BURST. Lucas raises a webbed hand, and the camera GLITCHES slightly.\n\nLUCAS\nDon’t. Real world’s not verified.\n\nMark freezes mid-stand. He looks at the camera—his expression is one of pure, exhausted resignation. He slowly sits back down on the floor.\n\nDAVE\n(Looking at the ceiling)\nShould we... leave?\n\nLUCAS\n(Staring at the lens)\nRedacting.\n\nLucas lets out a deep, bass-boosted RIBBIT that sounds like a corporate jingle. The screen CUTS TO BLACK instantly.",
